race.comment: TIME TO BACA (6) improved to score by half a length as the public elect over this trip, and it was a tough effort from a wide gate. Draws inside today and is well placed again with the 3kg claim. She can go on with the job. KING AKEED (1) resumes and has switched from a Western Australian yard. Has an awkward gate, but he's raced well in stronger than this, and it's a matter of readiness. MR NUNEZ (5) won his Maiden easily, spiking his figures. Has a soft barrier and will be in the finish holding that form. SASS (8) is still a Maiden but the former NSW galloper is going well. Has a senior hoop on today and should be around the mark.
